{
  "texts": [
    "The lower envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution (roughly coinciding with the R EXT Hα = 0.05 × R median Hα line in Figure 7) is influenced by the R EXT Hα > 3 × δR EXT Hα screening condition and mostly a truncation effect; while the top envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution exhibits fine structures, which have physical implications.",
    "As displayed in Figure 7, the top envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution first increases with log R median Hα, reaching the R EXT Hα = 0.35 × R median Hα line around log R median Hα ∼ -5.1, and then decreases with the increase of log R median Hα from about log R median Hα ∼ -5.0.",
    "At about log R median Hα = -4.85 (indicated by a short arrow in Figure 7), the top envelope turns to gradually increase with log R median Hα, and it is largely along a positive correlation line for log R median Hα > -4.85.",
    "The different behaviors of the top envelope on the left side and right side of the turning position (short arrow) might be related to the stratification of activity levels of solar-like stars, which will be further discussed in Section 6.",
    "In the following analysis, the stellar sources on the left side (log R median Hα < -4.85; with lower activity intensity) and right side (log R median Hα > -4.85; with higher activity intensity) of the top envelope turning position will be distinguished where appropriate, owing to their different behaviors of Hα variability."
  ]
}